{
  "texts": [
    "The MRT is a variation of the Diagnostic Rhyme Test (DRT) [3], which only presents listeners with two possible choices.",
    "Positive aspects of the modified rhyme test are that it is reliable as well as easy to conduct.",
    "Its drawbacks are that the test scenario is unrealistic compared to actual use cases for synthesized speech, and this limited scenario results in artificially high scores.",
    "The multiple-choice paradigm also does not reveal confusions that listeners may have made that are not pre-sented among the six choices.",
    "Furthermore, consonant clusters are not evaluated in a standard MRT."
  ]
}